:"Ps.76.4","text":"Thou art more glorious and excellent than the mountains of prey."},{"id":"rec5JMVMidzARYo5J","ref":"Ps.76.5","text":"The stouthearted are spoiled, they have slept their sleep: and none of the men of might have found their hands."},{"id":"recY05i63pTF9mCmn","ref":"Ps.76.6","text":"At thy rebuke, O God of Jacob, both the chariot and horse are cast into a dead sleep."},{"id":"reciYUOeXtZnq03iN","ref":"Ps.76.7","text":"Thou, even thou, art to be feared: and who may stand in thy sight when once thou art angry?"},{"id":"recvyYyatrq3QIki2","ref":"Ps.76.8","text":"Thou didst cause judgment to be heard from heaven; the earth feared, and was still,"}]}
